This paper discusses the privacy implications of encrypting DNS traffic, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses traffic analysis, which is a subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and information security (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses machine learning classifiers, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data.
